My friends and I had an hour to kill before the Elite Great Gatsby Yelp Event.
So after a stop at the sex shop down the street, which is a whole other story, we stopped in here for a drink.
Now I am not a coffee person at all.
Not even close.
The closest I will get to coffee is a frappuccino which is nowhere near coffee which is why I like it.
I was looking over the menu looking for anything I might like and noticed they had Italian Soda.
Hey that sounds good.
The woman behind the counter, who was very nice, realized that we were newbies so she explained how things worked.
Basically you can get any flavor you want in any drink you want.
So I settled on a peppermint Italian Soda.
The prices I noticed were very cheap for a coffee place.
I was expecting smaller sizes for that price but no I ordered a medium and it was pretty big.
Much bigger than I expected.
Plus with 10% off for checking in it was great.
Once I placed my order my drink was made very quickly and with a great attitude.
It tasted great.
Cool and refreshing and it hit the spot.
After looking over the other reviews I wonder if I went to the same place because I had a great experience and would go back again if I was ever in that neighborhood.
Maybe I went on a good day or they have straighten things out or something.
But for the price and the taste of my drink I would definitely recommend it.

