I've always loved Hava Java- if I lived closer, I would prob be there daily and develop an addiction.
When I heard they had recently undated their interior I thought I would drive over and check it out.
Upon entering, it was caffeinetastic to see the place packed.
Each table was filled with someone typing away on their electronic device or chatting away.
I loved the sense of coziness- like you could sit there all day if you should choose.
Being summer, I decided to order an iced coffee and it was delish!
Just the right amount of flavor and just what I needed!
I also loved the new bar area.
Modernized yet still matching the existing decor.
I also like how clean everything felt.
That's important for me anywhere I go.
I think Hava Java has been around a long time.
I can see why- and I see them being around for many years to come.
Can't go wrong coming here for a cup of Jo.
And if you check in on Yelp, it's 10% off your bill!

